{"id": "6159", "post": "<div class=\"post-6159 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-editorial tag-community-roundup-2\" id=\"post-6159\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/community-roundup-december-2014/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Community Roundup \u2013 December 2014</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" alt=\"Tags: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/community-roundup-2/\" rel=\"tag\">community roundup</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" alt=\"Date/Time: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> January 2, 2015 @ 1:00 am, by Maarten Kossen</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p>It\u2019s time for another community update! This time I\u2019ll cover December 2014 and highlight some notable events as well as some plans we have for the future.</p><h2>Holidays</h2><p>While they technically started in November, December is holiday month and we\u2019ve had thanksgiving, Christmas, and New Year\u2019s Eve. We\u2019ve seen some nice offers during Thanksgiving as well as during Christmas and I hope you\u2019ve all enjoyed them. Next year I\u2019m looking to make the holiday season even more interesting, so feel free to send me any feedback for that.</p><h2>Shared/Reseller hosting trial</h2><p>Though it had a bit of a bumpy start and the rules were changed after a few days based on valuable community feedback, shared and reseller hosting offers are now allowed on LowEndTalk <em>only</em> if a provider also has an active VPS offering. In a couple of weeks time we\u2019ll be evaluating this and requesting your feedback to see where we\u2019ll go in the future.</p><p><span id=\"more-6159\"></span></p><h2>New hosts featured on LowEndBox</h2><p>The following new hosts were featured on LowEndBox:</p><ol><li><a title=\"Berry Servers \u2013 3 annual offers starting at $6/year for a 64MB OVZ in Phoenix\" href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/berry-servers-3-annual-offers-starting-at-6year-for-a-64mb-ovz-in-phoenix/\">Berry.pw</a> (though technically a subsidiary of Epidrive)</li><li><a title=\"Media-Hosts \u2013 CAD$7/month or CAD$48/year 512MB OVZ in Ottowa, Canada\" href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/media-hosts-cad7month-or-cad48year-512mb-ovz-in-ottowa-canada/\">Media-Hosts</a></li><li><a title=\"Mean Servers \u2013 KVMs in Denver \u2013 $5/month 512MB and $7/month 1GB\" href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/mean-servers-kvms-in-denver-5month-512mb-and-7month-1gb/\">Mean Servers</a></li><li><a title=\"VikingLayer \u2013 3 OpenVZ offers in France starting at $14.95/year for 256MB\" href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/vikinglayer-3-openvz-offers-in-france-starting-at-14-95year-for-256mb/\">Viking Layer</a></li><li><a title=\"IndoVirtue \u2013 $7/month OpenVZ SSD Singapore\" href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/indovirtue-7month-openvz-ssd-singapore/\">IndoVirtue</a></li><li><a title=\"HostSailor \u2013 $2.99/month 512MB OVZ in Amsterdam and more\" href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/hostsailor-2-99month-512mb-ovz-in-amsterdam-and-more/\">HostSailor</a></li></ol><p>That\u2019s a lot of new hosts in one month and I hope you guys all appreciate that!</p><h2>Improvements in posts</h2><p>We\u2019ve started to slowly improve the offering on LowEndBox and the quality of posts. Almost every post is now written from scratch; this has been different for a while due to time constraints. Unfortunately, copy-pasting posts leads to bad quality posts and it doesn\u2019t do the site much good either.</p><p>We\u2019ve also started feverishly denying repeat offers in the helpdesk. We\u2019ve looking to feature different offers each and every time. Reasons to feature a host are: a new location, overhauled product lines, considerably hardware improvements, considerable plan changes, or special pricing/account credits. Minor changes to pricing or offerings are considered repeat offers as are repeated offers for free account credit. I really hope we can diversify LowEndBox more this way. As usual, any feedback is appreciated.</p><p class=\"dpsp-share-text\"></p><div id=\"dpsp-content-bottom\" class=\"dpsp-content-wrapper dpsp-shape-rounded dpsp-column-auto dpsp-has-spacing dpsp-no-labels dpsp-show-on-mobile dpsp-button-style-1 dpsp-has-icon-background dpsp-has-button-background dpsp-show-total-share-count dpsp-show-total-share-count-after\"><ul class=\"dpsp-networks-btns-wrapper dpsp-networks-btns-content dpsp-has-button-icon-animation\"><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Fcommunity-roundup-december-2014%2F&amp;t=Community%20Roundup%20-%20December%202014\" class=\"dpsp-network-btn dpsp-facebook dpsp-no-label dpsp-first\" title=\"Share on Facebook\"><span class=\"dpsp-network-icon\"></span><span class=\"dpsp-network-label-wrapper\"></span></a></li><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Community%20Roundup%20-%20December%202014&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Fcommunity-roundup-december-2014%2F&amp;via=LowEndNetwork\" class=\"dpsp-network-btn dpsp-twitter dpsp-no-label\" title=\"Share on Twitter\"><span class=\"dpsp-network-icon\"></span><span class=\"dpsp-network-label-wrapper\"></span></a></li><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?url=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Fcommunity-roundup-december-2014%2F&amp;title=Community%20Roundup%20-%20December%202014&amp;mini=true\" class=\"dpsp-network-btn dpsp-linkedin dpsp-no-label dpsp-last\" title=\"Share on LinkedIn\"><span class=\"dpsp-network-icon\"></span><span class=\"dpsp-network-label-wrapper\"></span></a></li></ul><div class=\"dpsp-total-share-wrapper\"><span class=\"dpsp-icon-total-share\"></span><span class=\"dpsp-